<BaseLayout
  title="About Little Boracay Calatagan, Batangas"
  description="About Little Boracay — the natural sandbar destination in Calatagan, Batangas and LittleBoracay.com, the dedicated information platform for travelers."
>

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="badge badge-ocean">About</span>
    <h1>About Little Boracay</h1>
    <p class="page-lead">Little Boracay is one of the most recognized sandbar destinations in Calatagan, Batangas — and LittleBoracay.com is dedicated to helping travelers discover and visit it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container about-grid">
    <div>
      <h2>About the Destination</h2>
      <p><strong>Little Boracay</strong> is a natural tidal sandbar located off the western coastline of Calatagan, Batangas, facing the South China Sea. Known for its clear shallow waters, wide white sand areas, and iconic floating bamboo cottages anchored offshore, the destination has become a popular coastal escape for travelers throughout the Philippines.</p>
      <p>The sandbar sits within the coastal municipality of Calatagan, a growing tourism area in southern Luzon known for its beaches, fishing communities, and relaxed atmosphere. Little Boracay draws visitors for day trips, family outings, group celebrations, and photography expeditions.</p>
      <p>The destination's beauty lies in its natural, undeveloped character. Unlike resort beaches, Little Boracay is shaped by the tides — the sandbar appears and changes throughout the day, creating an ever-shifting landscape that rewards those who visit at the right moment.</p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:36px;">About LittleBoracay.com</h2>
      <p><strong>LittleBoracay.com</strong> is the dedicated online platform for information about Little Boracay in Calatagan, Batangas. As interest in the sandbar grows, travelers increasingly search for reliable, up-to-date information about how to visit, what to expect, and how to plan a trip.</p>
      <p>LittleBoracay.com was created to be that resource — a centralized, accurate, and helpful guide for anyone planning a trip to the Little Boracay sandbar.</p>

      <div class="vision-box">
        <h3>Our Vision</h3>
        <p>To be the most trusted online resource for Little Boracay — helping travelers explore the sandbar while supporting responsible tourism and awareness of Calatagan's coastal communities.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 style="margin-top:36px;">Connect With the Community</h2>
      <p>The Little Boracay online community spans thousands of travelers, beach lovers, and photographers who share their experiences and tips.</p>
      <div class="community-links">
